title: Attribute "JCabi-Revision" not found in MANIFEST.MF
body:
I can't run my test program with jcabi-github 0.7. On a line

``` java
Github github = new RtGithub(githubKey);
```

an exception occurs:

```
Caused by: java.lang.IllegalArgumentException: Atribute 'JCabi-Revision' not found in MANIFEST.MF file(s) among 47 other attribute(s) ["Ant-Version", "Archiver-Version", "Bnd-LastModified", "Build-Id", "Build-Jdk", "Built-By", "Built-Date", "Bundle-Activator", "Bundle-Description", "Bundle-DocURL", "Bundle-License", "Bundle-ManifestVersion", "Bundle-Name", "Bundle-RequiredExecutionEnvironment", "Bundle-SymbolicName", "Bundle-Vendor", "Bundle-Version", "Class-Path", "Created-By", "DynamicImport-Package", "Export-Package", "Extension-Name", "Ignore-Package", "Implementation-Build", "Implementation-Title", "Implementation-URL", "Implementation-Vendor", "Implementation-Vendor-Id", "Implementation-Version", "Import-Package", "Include-Resource", "JCabi-Build", "JCabi-Date", "JCabi-Version", "Manifest-Version", "Private-Package", "ReXSL-Build", "ReXSL-Date", "ReXSL-Version", "Sealed", "Specification-Title", "Specification-Vendor", "Specification-Version", "Tool", "X-Compile-Source-JDK", "X-Compile-Target-JDK", "url"] and 0 injection(s)
    at com.jcabi.manifests.Manifests.read(Manifests.java:210)
    at com.jcabi.github.RtGithub.<clinit>(RtGithub.java:77)
```

Looks like the "JCabi-Revision" attribute is expected. And by the way there is a typo in the exception message: "... Atribute 'Jcabi-Revision' ...".
